online access with authorization2star  aThis volume of essays intends to present diverse aspects of monotheistic kingship during the Middle Ages in two general-theoretical articles and a series of “case studies” on the relationship of religion and rulership. The authors discuss examples of the role of religion—based on both textual and iconic evidence—in Carolingian, Ottonian and late medieval western Europe; in Byzantium and Armenia; Georgia; Hungary; the Khazar Khanate; Poland, and Rus’. Two studies explore the issue in medieval Jewish and Islamic political thought. The editors hope that these special inquiries will engender more comparative studies on the subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aReligion.1 aAl-Azmeh, A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBak, János M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDalemki, Zbigniew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaripzanov, Ildar H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaspar, Cristian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeréby, György, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGussone, Nikolaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKapp Jr., Stephen H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaraulashvili, Irma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoreno-Riaño, Gerson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNemerkényi, Elöd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetrukhin, Vladimir Ja., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmelomzky, Ágoston, econtributor.4ctb4https://i